75 – 78
). Lateral scoli apically armed with pointed seta whereas lateral branches armed with elongate cauliflower-shape sensillum (
Figs 76 – 79
). Scoli of first two pairs placed very close to each other ( Figs 34 , 52, 53 ). Supra-anal processes short, as long as 3/5 of body length.

