Figs 65 – 67
).

Two pairs of minute setae at anterior border of pro-, meso- and metasternum. Pro-, meso- and metasternum also with two groups of numerous setae antero-medially (placed very close to each other) a pair of setae posteromedially and a group of cauliflower-shaped sensilla on each lateral side (
